{"error":0,"message":"","data":[{"show_ID":"2054","airdate":"1524592800","name_switch":"off","DJ":"ziona and Slaygon","showname":"Unusually Regular Request Show","blurb":"Hello Our Beloved SLAYPeeps! \n\nWe think last week we had a really pleasant conversation about sci-fi movies and novels, which unfortunately got lost in the virtual space as a recording, but those who were there seemed to enjoy it. \nSo we were thinking and got to a question: if we could talk so much stupid things if needed, why didn't we ever do a very USUAL, TYPICAL, NORMAL request show which does not have any specified topic or guest? \nPrepare yourself and your favourite tracks because _this is what we are going to try now_! \n\nOK, to make it just a little special you could give us a reason why you love the tune you have picked so much! =) \n\nGrab a drink, sit back, relax and enjoy SLAYing with us! \n\n","nice_showname":"<strong><big>ziona and Slaygon<\/big><\/strong><br \/>Unusually Regular Request Show","nice_airdate":"Tuesday 24th April, 2018<br \/>at 20:00 USRT"},{"show_ID":"2055","airdate":"1524679200","name_switch":"off","DJ":"Bozzy and the Bint","showname":"BBKB","blurb":"It's the taint of the week\u2122 again, so it's time for Boz to utter complete bollocks in between your requests. Thankfully, Kate is here to translate some of it into English. All aboard the Train-Wreck, WOO HOO!","nice_showname":"<strong><big>Bozzy and the Bint<\/big><\/strong><br \/>BBKB","nice_airdate":"Wednesday 25th April, 2018<br \/>at 20:00 USRT"}]}